libbdplus
------------------------------------------
This library is written for the purpose of playing Blu-ray movies. It is
intended for software that want to support Blu-ray playback (such as VLC and
MPlayer). We, the authors of this library, do not condone nor endorse piracy.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libbdplus-devel-0.2.0-1bl1
  libbdplus0-0.2.0-1bl1
  libgcrypt20-1.10.1-1
  libgpg-error0-1.37-1
  pkg-config-1.8.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-1
  automake-11-1
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.0-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libgcrypt-devel-1.10.1-1
  libgpg-error-devel-1.37-1
  libtool-2.4.7-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://www.videolan.org/developers/libbdplus.html

Canonical download:
  https://download.videolan.org/pub/videolan/libbdplus/0.2.0/libbdplus-0.2.0.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libbdplus-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libbdplus-0.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libbdplus-0.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbdplus-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbdplus0-0.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libbdplus-devel-0.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libbdplus)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libbdplus.README
  /usr/share/doc/libbdplus/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libbdplus/ChangeLog
  /usr/share/doc/libbdplus/README.md

(libbdplus0)
  /usr/bin/cygbdplus-0.dll

(libbdplus-devel)
  /usr/include/libbdplus/bdplus-version.h
  /usr/include/libbdplus/bdplus.h
  /usr/lib/libbdplus.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libbdplus.pc

